default              
defaultWhat are the main challenges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated communities?  How can these challenges be overcome?
default&#xa0;
defaultThere are no mainline rail 
defaultlinks in West Somerset; the closest mainline station is Taunton.  A heritage steam railway operates a tourist service along a 20 mile track between Minehead and Bishop Lydeard.  The track is connected to the mainline at Taunton but is used very infrequentl
defaulty for tourist services.  There would be potential to bring a commuter rail service into West Somerset with sufficient finances – reducing the traffic and CO
default2
default emissions on the busy A358.
default&#xa0;
defaultThere is one viable bus service which runs between Minehead and Taunt
defaulton.  All other public transport services in West Somerset are subsidised.  SCC is considering axing many of these services in the future to reduce their costs.
defaultc
defaultont
defaultd..
default.
defaultTo our knowledge no mapping of the present service provision has taken place in the 
defaultdistrict, so it is not possible to confidently identify where the gaps in provision are.
default&#xa0;
defaultTransport provision is a huge issue in the district and Clinical Commissioning, Public Health, MIND, Somerset Sight and the Alzheimer's Society all share our concerns
default about the poor public transport 
defaultservice which is available across a
default large area of our district.
